DESCRIPTION:<b>REGISTRATION</b>: <a href="https://duke.is/v/h2eq" target="
 _blank">Click Here</a>\n\n<i>Registration closes 24 hours before event st
 art. If your availability changes please email asist@duke.edu to update y
 our registration. Detailed directions\, instructions for free parking\, a
 nd any prep material will be emailed out one week and one day before the 
 event.</i>\n\nTired of zoom rooms and online trainings? <b>Join us in per
 son on March 17th 12:15-1:45 pm</b> for a structured conversation to disc
 uss and explore the experiences and challenges we have faced trying to ge
 t academic research published.\n\nTalking Circles are an event format off
 ered by ASIST that are designed to bring researchers across backgrounds a
 nd experience levels together to explore the intersection of research cul
 ture and research integrity. All participants will have the opportunity t
 o share their thoughts\, stories\, and perspectives. <i>This is not a lec
 ture-style event.</i> \n\nParticipation in this event fulfills the <b>RCR
 -200</b> requirement for Faculty and Staff and the <b>714 RCR credit</b> 
 for graduate students. Due to the nature of structured conversation\, par
 ticipants will not be able to join after the event has begun. Participant
 s must be present for the entire event to receive credit.\n\nContact:\nAS
 IST\nasist@duke.edu
DURATION:PT1H30M
DTSTAMP:20260312T161652Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260317T121500
LAST-MODIFIED:20260312T161652Z
