DESCRIPTION:This session is designed for biomedical researchers seeking to
  broaden their funding portfolio and enhance the real-world impact of the
 ir work. Explore how partnerships with foundations\, industry\, and other
  non-federal sponsors can open new avenues of support for innovative biom
 edical projects. Participants will learn effective strategies for identif
 ying funding opportunities\, building collaborative relationships with po
 tential sponsors\, and aligning their research objectives with diverse fu
 nding priorities to drive discovery and innovation.
DURATION:PT1H
